<document>

  <properties>
    <title>New run discovering</title>
    <author email="jourdren@biologie.ens.fr">Laurent Jourdren</author>
  </properties>

  <body>
    <section name="New run discovering step">

       <p>This step checks if a new run is currently running.
          With a HiSeq sequencer if the first base report has been generated, if true, sends an email with the first base report.
          With a NextSeq sequencer, first base report has not been generated, Aozan checks existence on first file created by sequence.
         If true sends an email with main feature on the new run.
         </p>

       <h4>Configuration parameters</h4>

     <p>The next table contains the parameters of this step.</p>

       <table>
         <tr><th>Aozan property</th><th>Type</th><th>Default value</th><th>description</th></tr>
         <tr><td>first.base.report.step</td><td>boolean</td><td>True</td><td>Enable the step</td></tr>
     </table>
       <p>Example of email sent for the new run discovering step</p>
      <div align="center">
      <table>
        <tr><th>Example on HiSeq run with First base report</th><th>Example on NextSeq run</th></tr>
        <tr style="text-align:center; background-color: #FFFFFF"><td>
        <img src="images/mail_firstbasereport_450px.png" alt="example mail on HiSeq run with First base report" style="vertical-align:middle"/>
        </td><td>
           <img src="images/mail_newrun_nextseq.png"
           alt="example mail on NextSeq run"  border="1"/>
          </td></tr></table>
        </div>

       </section>

  </body>

